This paper deals with privacy concerns in the context of travel data collection, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also discusses methods for preserving utility and randomness in the distribution of perturbation distances, which are relevant to the database (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of location data and probability distributions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
